    <introduction>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>Queen Margaret University has the opportunity to nominate two individuals for the prestigious Carnegie Trust PhD scholarship scheme for study commencing in September 2018. The prospective candidates must hold, or expect to gain, a first class Honours undergraduate degree from a Scottish University and wish to complete the Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) programme at Queen Margaret University.</p>
<p> The Carnegie Trust makes no restriction on the subject or field. However, in order to be supported by QMU, the PhD topic must be in an area that is aligned with one of the University’s <a href="/{localLink:umb://document/111619e552024b8e9010a77021ca06c9}" title="Research Centres, Institutes and Knowledge Exchange Centres">Research Centres</a>.</p>]]></Value>
    </introduction>
